   "source": [
    "# Antenna Panel"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "efec1d0e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import scipy.io\n",
    "\n",
    "import neoradium as nr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "0b128508",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# We first create an antenna element template. The antenna panel class \"AntennaPanel\" uses this\n",
    "# template to create the elements of the panel.\n",
    "elementTemplate = nr.AntennaElement(beamWidth=[65,65], maxAttenuation=30)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now we can create the antenna panel using the antenna element template. Note that the spacing between the\n",
    "# elements is 0.5𝜆 by default.\n",
    "panel = nr.AntennaPanel([4,4], elements=elementTemplate, polarization=\"+\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# The \"showElements\" method draws the antenna panel showing all the elements.\n",
    "panel.showElements(zeroTicks=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "4cd1fb53",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Depending on the input parameters the \"drawRadiation\" method can create different types of graphs. Here\n",
    "# we draw the Field values of the antenna panel at the horizontal plane of zero elevation.\n",
    "radValues = panel.drawRadiation(theta=90, viewAngles=(90,0), radiationType=\"Field\", normalize=False)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "e6124e66",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Here the \"drawRadiation\" method is used to draw the Field values in the vertical plane at azimuth angle 0.\n",
    "radValues = panel.drawRadiation(phi=0, radiationType=\"Field\", normalize=False)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "e9ba94d1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Here the \"drawRadiation\" method is used to draw a 3D graph of directivity.\n",
    "radValues = panel.drawRadiation(radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=True, viewAngles=(60,10))\n"
   ]
  },
